                           <p part="N"/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Notes indicating the readings are written (in red ink) in the upper margin of some fols.: &#xD;
mǝnbab zä-ʾǝhud zä-sǝrk: fol 4v &#xD;
ʾorit zä-sämunä ḥǝmamat: fol. 10v&#xD;
mǝnbab zä-sänuy: fol. 11r&#xD;
bä-sälästä, bä-qätr, bä-säʾat (upper margin), bä-śärk (between columns): fol. 118v&#xD;
zä-näwam, bä-lelit (between columns): fol. 119r&#xD;
- Titles of the subsections are repeated in the left margins of the columns in fols. 70rc-74rb.&#xD;
- Texts II-1, II-3, II-4 are included in the readings for Friday.&#xD;
- Crude notes on fols.1r-1v (pen trials?), 58v, 59r, 113v, 114v (in blue pen), 76v (in pencil), 139v.&#xD;
- Oversized bold letters in fol. 141r.  &#xD;
- Unfilled space left for rubrication in fols. 47rb, 119rb.&#xD;
- Cues for the titles of the works and and directives for the ministers, starting from fol. 120r (?).&#xD;
- Empty space left in fol. 119rb. &#xD;
- Thread for navigating in the text inserted in fols. 60, 113, 140 (?). &#xD;
- Pen trials in fols. 141r.</item>
